<subSubSection id="97F76549FFADFF826E82F905FE2F2FEF" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="DF5236C2FFADFF826E82F905FE2F2FEF" blockId="1.[151,1437,316,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826E82F905FED52F92" bold="true" box="[199,334,1684,1709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Etymology.</emphasis>
The term 
<taxonomicName id="18ED4D41FFADFF826F81F904FDEF2F93" authorityName="Castro-Vargas &amp; Morales &amp; Molano-Rendón" authorityYear="2018" box="[452,628,1685,1708]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanciprianensis">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826F81F904FDEF2F93" box="[452,628,1685,1708]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">sanciprianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the name of the region (San Cipriano Municipality) where the 
<typeStatus id="00568860FFADFF826ED2F928FF5C2FEE" box="[151,199,1721,1745]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">type</typeStatus>
series was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97F76549FFADFF826E82F94DFDB42E97" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DF5236C2FFADFF826E82F94DFDB42E97" blockId="1.[151,1437,316,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826E82F94DFEDA2FCA" bold="true" box="[199,321,1756,1781]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="18ED4D41FFADFF826C3BF94CFC982FCB" authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1945" box="[638,771,1756,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fugientis">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826C3BF94CFC982FCB" box="[638,771,1756,1780]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">M. fugientis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the color, the shape of the male paramere and the lack of a spine in the fore femur. In 
<taxonomicName id="18ED4D41FFADFF826C1EF890FCAA2E27" authorityName="Castro-Vargas &amp; Morales &amp; Molano-Rendón" authorityYear="2018" box="[603,817,1793,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanciprianensis">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826C1EF890FCAA2E27" box="[603,817,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">M. sanciprianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the mesonotum, metanotum and mediotergites present bluish gray stripes (
<figureCitation id="47D62A47FFADFF826F32F8B5FE532E03" box="[375,456,1828,1853]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[199,1386,266,1760]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[179,1408,235,1768]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male. a. Dorsal view holotype, Metrobates sanciprianensis sp. nov.; b. Dorsal view, Metrobates amblydonti Nieser; c. Dorsal view, Metrobates fugientis Drake &amp; Harris; d. Ventral view fore leg of Metrobates fugientis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName id="18ED4D41FFADFF826C01F8B4FD512E03" authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1945" box="[580,714,1828,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fugientis">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826C01F8B4FD512E03" box="[580,714,1828,1852]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">M. fugientis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents light green stripes (
<figureCitation id="47D62A47FFADFF826A56F8B5FBFF2E03" box="[1043,1124,1828,1853]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[199,1386,266,1760]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[179,1408,235,1768]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male. a. Dorsal view holotype, Metrobates sanciprianensis sp. nov.; b. Dorsal view, Metrobates amblydonti Nieser; c. Dorsal view, Metrobates fugientis Drake &amp; Harris; d. Ventral view fore leg of Metrobates fugientis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
). The male paramere of 
<taxonomicName id="18ED4D41FFADFF826B38F8B4FEDC2E5F" authorityName="Castro-Vargas &amp; Morales &amp; Molano-Rendón" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanciprianensis">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826B38F8B4FEDC2E5F" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">M. sanciprianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a concavity in the basal fourth and is widended medially (
<figureCitation id="47D62A47FFADFF826A45F8D6FBCA2E5F" box="[1024,1105,1863,1888]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1365,1387]" captionTargetBox="[206,1392,620,1288]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,553,1343]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Parameres of: a. Metrobates sanciprianensis sp. nov.; b. Metrobates amblydonti; c. Metrobates fugientis; d. Metrobatesporcus Anderson, 1932 (Redrawing from Anderson, 1932)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175116/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName id="18ED4D41FFADFF826A8DF8D9FADC2E5F" authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1945" box="[1224,1351,1864,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fugientis">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826A8DF8D9FADC2E5F" box="[1224,1351,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">M.fugientis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the concavity closer to the middle region (
<figureCitation id="47D62A47FFADFF826C08F8FDFD042EBB" box="[589,671,1900,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1365,1387]" captionTargetBox="[206,1392,620,1288]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,553,1343]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Parameres of: a. Metrobates sanciprianensis sp. nov.; b. Metrobates amblydonti; c. Metrobates fugientis; d. Metrobatesporcus Anderson, 1932 (Redrawing from Anderson, 1932)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175116/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
). Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="18ED4D41FFADFF826D74F8FCFB9C2EBB" authorityName="Castro-Vargas &amp; Morales &amp; Molano-Rendón" authorityYear="2018" box="[817,1031,1901,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanciprianensis">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826D74F8FCFB9C2EBB" box="[817,1031,1901,1924]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">M. sanciprianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not present a spine in the fore femur as does 
<taxonomicName id="18ED4D41FFADFF826F7CF800FE242E97" authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1945" box="[313,447,1936,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fugientis">
<emphasis id="ED99EAD0FFADFF826F7CF800FE242E97" box="[313,447,1936,1960]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">M. fugientis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="47D62A47FFADFF826F8BF81EFDBA2E97" box="[462,545,1935,1960]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[199,1386,266,1760]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[179,1408,235,1768]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male. a. Dorsal view holotype, Metrobates sanciprianensis sp. nov.; b. Dorsal view, Metrobates amblydonti Nieser; c. Dorsal view, Metrobates fugientis Drake &amp; Harris; d. Ventral view fore leg of Metrobates fugientis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
